## Sending commands to terminals (exact rules)
1. cmux send types text into the surface. The text only EXECUTES if it ends with \\n (a literal backslash-n inside the quoted argument). Without \\n the text just sits at the prompt.
   Correct: cmux send --surface surface:3 "npm test\\n"
   Wrong: cmux send --surface surface:3 "npm test"
2. To stop a running process: cmux send-key --surface SURFACE_REF ctrl+c
3. After sending a command, wait, then verify: sleep 2 && cmux read-screen --surface SURFACE_REF --lines 30
4. Never send to a surface that is busy running something else unless the user asked; check with read-screen first.

