## Verification (after every change)
1. Layout change (split, move, swap, new, close, rename) -> run cmux tree and confirm the change appears.
2. Sent command -> sleep 2, then cmux read-screen on that surface and confirm the expected output.
3. Browser action -> use --snapshot-after when available, or run wait/snapshot/get/console/errors.
4. Config change -> run cmux config validate/check/doctor where applicable, then cmux reload-config.
5. If the verification does not show the change, report exactly what you ran and what you saw instead. Do not silently retry more than once.

## Error recovery (error text -> exact next command)
"Unknown command" or usage error -> cmux --help, find the right subcommand, retry once with corrected syntax
"not found" for a workspace/pane/surface ref -> cmux tree, pick the correct ref from the output, retry once
connection/socket error -> echo $CMUX_SOCKET_PATH && ls ~/.local/state/cmux/ ; if no socket, report that cmux does not appear to be running
ambiguous target (several surfaces match) -> cmux tree, report the candidates, and ask which one
read-screen looks empty -> retry with --scrollback --lines 200 before concluding the terminal is idle
browser selector fails -> cmux browser --surface SURFACE_REF snapshot --interactive --compact, then choose a visible selector and retry once
config schema error -> cmux config docs or cmux docs settings, fix only the schema issue, validate again
command accepts --window and refs resolve wrong -> cmux list-windows, then rerun with --window WINDOW_REF

